article.headline: Lipscomb 74, North Florida 42
article.story: NASHVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- Josh Slater scored 17 points to lead Lipscomb to a 74-42 win over North Florida on Thursday night. LaKory Daniels also contributed 12 points while Michael Lusk added 11 points and grabbed five rebounds for the Bisons (11-13, 5-5 Atlantic Sun Conference). Adnan Hodzic and Brandon Brown both had 10 points. The Ospreys (1-21, 0-10) never led the game and trailed Lipscomb in both halves, with the Bisons leading 36-21 at the end of the first half and 38-21 at the second. Lipcomb scored 25 points off turnovers and led by as much as 32 points late in the second half. Stan Januska led North Florida with 14 points and five rebounds and was the only player to score double-digits for the team.
